FBIS4-18247 "drweu063_l_94003" FBIS-WEU-94-063 Daily Report 30 Mar 1994 SPAIN Solana on Algerian Emigrant Problem Solana on Algerian Emigrant Problem LD3003223894 Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network in Spanish 2100 GMT 30 Mar 94 LD3003223894 Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network Spanish BFN [Text] In Washington, Spanish Foreign Minister Javier Solana, who met the U.S. secretary of state, has commented on the ongoing situation in Algeria and more specifically on the crowds of Algerians requesting entry visas to our country at the Spanish consulate over the last few days. [Begin Solana recording] If there are massive immigration movements -- massive waves -- we will have to consider the situation collectively. Migration to a Community country entails a Community policy decision. So we will have to consider the problem in Community terms. [end recording]
